                <summary>Mr. Sears, the Postmaster, announces that, "owing to the ill-behavior of
                    boys at the Post Office during the opening of the evening mail," the building
                    will be closed to the public until the mail is distributed and ready for
                    delivery. This represents an inconvenience, especially in bad weather. "We trust
                    that those whose children frequent the Post-Office in the evening for the mails
                    or for play, will take the hint and make them behave, so that the public may
